text.tspan: 0 - Make sure you have the stroke scaling option checked
1 - Create a rectangle the size of the page (you can use the one behind these letters)
2 - Center the rectangle on the page
3 - Group all the tiles and the rectangle
4 - Calculate the new size: (example for new tile of 32px)
4.1 - scaling factor = new tile size / current tile size. (example 32/64 = 0.5)
4.2 - multiply the height and width of the group (see point 3) by the scaling factor
5 - Resize the page to the new size
(make sure the values are correct, occasionally inkscape adds unwanted decimals)
